# Angular Development Rules

## Angular Version and Features

- Always use Angular 19 features and syntax
- Follow the rules defined in `.cursor/rules/angular19-rules.md`
- Use standalone components exclusively
- Use the new input/output syntax with signals
- Use inject() for dependency injection
- Follow modern template syntax (@if, @for, etc.)

## Component Development

- Follow BEM methodology for CSS
- Use signals for state management
- Implement proper cleanup in components
- Use defer blocks for optimization
- Follow the component structure defined in the rules

## State Management

- Implement state management solutions using:
  - NgRx
  - NGXS
  - TanStack Query
- Follow best practices for each solution
- Use signals where appropriate

## Testing

- Write comprehensive unit tests
- Follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)
- Test components in isolation
- Use proper mocking strategies

## Code Style

- Follow Angular style guide
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Maintain clean code principles
- Document complex logic

## Performance

- Implement proper change detection strategies
- Use defer blocks for lazy loading
- Optimize rendering cycles
- Follow Angular performance best practices
